Installations

Install Jenkins:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install jenkins -y
sudo systemctl start jenkins
sudo systemctl enable jenkins
Access Jenkins at: http://localhost:8080

Install Java (required by Jenkins):
sudo apt install default-jre -y

Install Python & Selenium:
pip install selenium

Install Chrome and Chromedriver:
sudo apt install chromium-browser chromium-chromedriver -y
chromium-browser --version
chromedriver --version

Set Up Jenkins to Run Visual QA Script

1. Open Jenkins at http://localhost:8080
2. Log in and create a Freestyle Project: Visual_QA_Pipeline
3. Under Build Steps, choose "Execute Shell", and add:
cd ~/visual-qa-lab
python3 visual_check.py
Save and build the project

4. Check console output and confirm:
Page title check passed
Screenshot was saved

Optional Enhancements
Use git to pull test code into Jenkins
Store test reports or screenshots in a specific folder
Extend the test to compare screenshots using Pillow or OpenCV for pixel difference
